Coercion of `baz` from fn item to fn pointer works only when `Bar` is implemented for `Foo` once. Adding any other implementation breaks coercion and requires manual cast. [Playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?gist=59a53d2e860d39ef50145b89391f08b9)
```rust
fn main() {
    Foo.bar(baz); // Causes error
    Foo.bar(baz as fn());
}

struct Foo;

trait Bar<T> {
    fn bar(&self, _: T) {}
}

impl Bar<fn()> for Foo {}
impl Bar<()> for Foo {} // Commenting it fixes error

fn baz() {}
```
Error:
```
error[E0277]: the trait bound `Foo: Bar<fn() {baz}>` is not satisfied
 --> src/main.rs:2:9
  |
2 |     Foo.bar(baz); // Causes error
  |         ^^^ the trait `Bar<fn() {baz}>` is not implemented for `Foo`
  |
  = help: the following implementations were found:
            <Foo as Bar<()>>
            <Foo as Bar<fn()>>
```
